      "content": "That makes sense. My main concern is the inspection process itself. If the inspector notices these small, unauthorized protrusions or items that have \"encroached\" into the setback area—like small storage sheds or even just some landscaping—is there a threshold where they stop viewing it as a minor oversight and start treating it like a more serious, unauthorized presence in the zone? Like, is there a point where the \"presence\" of these non-conforming elements becomes a major issue for the property owner?",
